  "version": "1.1.0",
  "version_notes": "v1.1.0 (2026-04-27, pre-fetch addendum pass): §A1 word-boundary skill matching (optional `match_mode` on SkillEntry; auto-classified for ≤4-char or all-caps forms; trailing 's' allowed for plurals). §A2 regex-based experience disqualifier with proximity-to-required-word gate; `description_disqualifiers.experience` now an object {max_years_allowed: 3, patterns: [...]}. §A3 + §B3 rule-based tags (top-level `tags` block) evaluated independently of titleTier; legacy HEALTHCARE_CONTEXT tag retired; tier C/D `tag` field kept as fallback. §A5 Tier A title list extended with hyperscaler 'engineer' titles (Microsoft/Google/Meta/AWS). §B4 employer_watchlist.categories restructured to {is_healthcare, employers} so §A4 can use a healthcare-employer match as a Tier D gate signal. KNOWN ISSUE (§A6, queued for post-fetch tuning): OSHA 10, NFPA 70E, EPA 608 appear in BOTH core_skills and certifications and currently double-count (8 + 5 = 13 pts per single mention). Per Imran 2026-04-27 this is unintended; will be deduplicated in §C. v1.0.0 was the initial taxonomy derived from UCI 2137 (15 weeks, 412.5 instructional hours).",
  "curriculum_source": {
    "course_code": "UCI 2137",
    "course_title": "Critical Facilities Technician",
    "duration_weeks": 15,
    "total_hours": 412.5,
    "certifications": ["OSHA-10", "NFPA 70E", "EPA 608"],
    "soc_codes": ["49-2095", "49-9041", "51-8013"],
